// 1) sort the array. this way if you have ["hall", "hallow", "hat"]
// it would sort it so that hat is first and hallow is last
// 2) Compare only first and last element. Because the longest posssible prefix will
// be at the end and the shorest possible prefix will be in the begining
// 3) convert first and last element to char array
// 4) loop through first elemnt comparing each value to last element value
// 5)Make sure that when looping you do not go-out-of-bounds for the last element
// 6) if it is equal then append it to a string builder
// if it is not equal immediately return the result

