This solution is the <b>vertical scanning</b> approach that is discussed in the official solution, slightly modified for Python.  The idea is to scan the the first character of every word, then the second character, etc. until a mismatch is found.  At that point, we return a slice of the string which is the longest common prefix.

This is superior to horizontal scanning because even if a very short word is included in the array, the algorithm won't do any extra work scanning the longer words and will still end when the end of the shortest word is reached.

