# C++ 100% Faster Solution Explained
Write a function to find the longest common prefix string amongst an array of strings.
If there is no common prefix, return an empty string "".
## Ex:

	Input: strs = ["flower","flow","flight"]
	Output: "fl"

## Solution Logic:
The coding for this solution is easy using the <b><a href="https://www.cplusplus.com/doc/tutorial/control/">For Loop</a></b> to handle iteration. When we focus on the logic behind this problem, we must remember to account for all possible versions of the intput and how to deal with it:
### Iterating through everything - For Loops
<li>The <b>given vector has an undefined amount of elements</b>, and we must compare them all - therefore we cannot hardcode x number of comparisions between x number of strings
<li>We <b>only need to iterate to the end of one word</b> because <b>all words</b> must be equal - so if one word reaches the end, it cannot possibly be the same as the rest beyond its length
<li>Make sure the for-loops incase everything. <b>We must first iterate over the length of a string, then over the size of the vector</b> for desired results. Otherwise, if we swap the loops, the program will stop comparing the characters of the strings at the position equal to the length of the vector. EG: if we receive 3 strings of 10 letters each, the program will only compare the first 3 letters of each string rather than the entire string.
<br></br>

### How to Tell When We Found the Largest Prefix - If Statement
<li>We reach a <b>position where the character</b> at that position in every given string <b>is not the same</b>
<li>We <b>reach the end of any string</b> - as anything beyond it does not exist to be the same as other strings
<br></br>

	class Solution {
	public:
		string longestCommonPrefix(vector<string>& strs) {
			//pos keeps track of the end of the common prefix, starts at 0 since its a prefix
			for(int pos = 0; pos < strs[0].length(); ++pos) //iterates over the length of the first word
				for(int i = 1; i < strs.size(); ++i) //for all of the strings in the vector
					//compare each char of the first string to the char at the same pos in each following string
					//if we reach the end of any string or a pos where the chars do not match, we have the largest prefix
					if(pos == strs[i].length() || strs[i][pos] != strs[0][pos])
						return strs[0].substr(0, pos);
			return strs[0];
		}
	};

